{
  "document_id": "job-39",
  "title": "Job 39",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "“Do you know when the mountain goats give birth?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "Can you number the months that they fulfill,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "when they crouch to give birth to their offspring"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "Their young ones become strong; they grow up in the open;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "“Who has let the wild ass go free?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "to which I have given the steppe for its home,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "It scorns the tumult of the city;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "It ranges the mountains as its pasture,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "“Is the wild ox willing to serve you?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "Can you tie it in the furrow with ropes,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "Will you depend on it because its strength is great,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "Do you have faith in it that it will return"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "“The ostrich’s wings flap wildly,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "For it leaves its eggs to the earth"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "forgetting that a foot may crush them"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "It deals cruelly with its young, as if they were not its own;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "because God has made it forget wisdom"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "When it spreads its plumes aloft,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "“Do you give the horse its might?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "Do you make it leap like the locust?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "It paws violently, exults mightily;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "It laughs at fear and is not dismayed;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "Upon it rattle the quiver,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "With fierceness and rage it swallows the ground;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "When the trumpet sounds, it says ‘Aha!’"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "“Is it by your wisdom that the hawk soars"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "Is it at your command that the eagle mounts up"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "It lives on the rock and makes its home"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "From there it spies the prey;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-39-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "Its young ones suck up blood,"
    }
  ]
}